AL Zorah Villa Residential Project in Ajman, United Arab Emirates, has been launched by the Al Zorah Development Company which is a joint venture between Solidere International, a city maker, place maker, and developer focused on creating urban destinations and mixed-use real estate developments in the Middle East and emerging markets internationally, and the Government of Ajman. The project will be developed adjacent to The Oberoi Beach Resort, a retreat destination that boasts modern Italian architecture, a white sand beach, and harmony with nature and heart. The AL Zorah Villa residential project in Ajman includes and features a limited number of 5,651 square feet of luxury villa units that span across an area of 10,000 square feet. The units have been designed with families taken into consideration. The CEO of Al Zorah, George Saad, stated that the development offers direct access to stunning views of the Arabian Gulf as well as access to a private beach. The CEO expressed that the villas would be an exciting opportunity for visitors and residents that seek exclusivity and privacy in a setting that has an urban feel while at the same time is natural. George added that in addition to the outdoor and indoor spaces, the project will also enable all visitors and residents to enjoy all the premium features that are within the exquisite Al Zorah destination. Also Read: Al Zorah Golf Clubhouse Construction in Ajman, UAE, Begins These premium features include but are not limited to the Al Zorah Golf Club alongside its 18-hole championship golf course, the Al Zorah Marina 1 & Park as well as the Oberoi Beach Resort. Set to be one of the most significant tourist destinations, Al Zorah is set to experience more construction of luxury resorts on the seashore. The project will also offer a secure, gated community accompanied by uninterrupted sea views.